=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=The+Nuer+of+the+Southern+Sudan&amp;rft.btitle=African+Political+Systems&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pages=272-96&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1940&amp;rft.aulast=Evans-Pritchard&amp;rft.aufirst=E.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fstream%2Fafricanpolitical00fort%23page%2F272%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACross-cutting+cleavage\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Gluckman, Max (1954). <i>\u2018Political Institutions\u2019, in E. E. Evans-Pritchard, ed., The Institutions of Primitive Society</i>. Glencoe, Ill.: The Free Press. pp.&#160;66\u201380.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%E2%80%98Political+Institutions%E2%80%99%2C+in+E.+E.+Evans-Pritchard%2C+ed.%2C+The+Institutions+of+Primitive+Society&amp;rft.place=Glencoe%2C+Ill.&amp;rft.pages=66-80&amp;rft.pub=The+Free+Press&amp;rft.date=1954&amp;rft.aulast=Gluckman&amp;rft.aufirst=Max&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACross-cutting+cleavage\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Kroeber, A. L. (1917). <i>Zu\u02dcni Kin and Clan</i>. New York: The Trustees of the American Museum of Natural History.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Zu%CB%9Cni+Kin+and+Clan&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=The+Trustees+of+the+American+Museum+of+Natural+History&amp;rft.date=1917&amp;rft.aulast=Kroeber&amp;rft.aufirst=A.+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACross-cutting+cleavage\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Lipset, Seymour Martin, and Stein Rokkan. 1967. \"Cleavage Structures, Party Systems,and Voter Alignments.\"  In: Party Systems and Voter Alignments: Cross-National Perspectives, eds. Seymour Martin Lipset and Stein Rokkan. New York: The Free Press\npp. 1\u201364.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Stein Rokkan, \"Geography,Religion and Social Class: Cross Cutting Cleavages in Norwegian Politics,\" in S. M. Lipset and S. Rokkan, eds., Party Systems and Voter Alignments (New York, 1967), 368-369</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Mutz, Diana C. (March 2002). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/crosscutting-social-networks-testing-democratic-theory-in-practice/2E570E31F3BB84B723CEF2A48A3C6741\">\"Cross-cutting Social Networks: Testing Democratic Theory in Practice\"</a>. <i>American Political Science Review</i>. <b>96</b> (1): 111\u2013126. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1017/S0003055402004264\">10.1017/S0003055402004264</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number\" title=\"International Standard Serial Number\">ISSN</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/issn/1537-5943\">1537-5943</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Ame